; classroom_config.cfg.example
;
; This is an example of the classroom_config.cfg format used by the
; GitHub Classroom Godot addon.
;
; HOW TO USE:
;   1. Copy or edit addons/github_classroom/classroom_config.cfg in your
;      template repository.
;   2. Fill in the values below (see descriptions).
;   3. Commit and push the file to your template repository on GitHub.
;   4. When students accept the GitHub Classroom assignment and clone the
;      repo, the addon will automatically read these values so students
;      never need to enter the Client ID or Organization themselves.
;
; FIELDS:
;   oauth_client_id  Your GitHub OAuth App Client ID.
;                    • Create one at: GitHub → Settings → Developer Settings
;                      → OAuth Apps → New OAuth App
;                    • The Client ID is a PUBLIC identifier (starts with Ov23li).
;                      It is safe to commit to a public or private repository.
;                    • Enables the "Sign in with GitHub" button for students
;                      without manual token setup.
;
;   organization     Your GitHub Classroom organization name, e.g. my-school-cs.
;                    Students will see this pre-filled in the Organization field.
;
; Both fields are optional.  If absent, students can fill in the fields manually.

[classroom]
oauth_client_id=Ov23liXXXXXXXXXXXXXX
organization=your-github-classroom-org
